						               													<description>Straight Shooter is a dexterity/shooting game with a wild west theme. Be the first to clear all of the pucks out of your area and win. Very similar to Fastrack, but for four players instead of two.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;A rootin' tootin' disc shootin' noggin' bootin' showdown.  How quick is yer draw?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This ain't no high-falutin' showdown for the sappy.  This here is the real deal, rootin' tootin' disc-shootin' that'll make an armadillo curl up and high-tail it home.  'Round here, yer either the best shot or you'll be buzzard food.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Not only are ya shootin' for braggin' rights, but straight shooter helps with the way yer hands and eyes coordinate.  An' don't even git me started on the benefits to yer visual perception, which helps fer when yer rindin' around town on horseback and other such activities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game itself is constructed of geen-u-wine wood, much finer than ol' man Jones' wooden leg.  If that don't make ya skip foer joy, then maybe ya been in the sun too long&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;1. Each player chooses a character and a town to represent.  Pick up all 5 pieces of yer ammo and place it in yer town.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. As soon as the rooster crows (or someone yells &amp;quot;DRAW&amp;quot;), y'all start shootin' into each other's towns by pushing down yer ammo and springin' it off yer trusty elastic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. First one of y'all to empty yer town of all the ammo (Yers or another player's) is the winner.  Then you git ta tell everybody else ta git outta Dodge!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
